    <div class="documentBody">
        
        <div>
            <p>The Office of the Prime Minister appointed Lotte Grepp Knutsen as State Secretary in the Ministry of Culture on 20 October 2009. From January to August in 2010 she was acting State Secretary at the Office of the Prime Minister.</p>
<p>Lotte Grepp Knutsen’s previous position was State Secretary in the Ministry of Children and Equality. Before that, she worked as Communications Adviser in JKL. She has also worked as Political Adviser in the Labour Party City Council Group in Oslo, and has worked with external and internal information in the Parliamentary Archives. She has a Masters Degree in Sociology from the University of Oslo. </p>
